    "At his death he was succeeded by <a href=\"/wolfflinh\">Heinrich W\u00f6lfflin</a>.": [],
    "His more famous students included <a href=\"/lichtwarka\">Alfred Lichtwark</a>; <a href=\"/meiergraefej\">Julius Meier-Graefe</a> studied under him but received not degree.": [],
    "Grimm's reputation is that of the arch-Romantic, <em>Gr\u00fcnderzeit</em> art historian.": [],
    "He viewed himself as the intellectual successor of Goethe.": [],
    "His approach to art history was through the \"Great Masters,\" and arranging significance of art through a biographical account of art history.": [],
    "His tastes both typified and led German and continental bourgeois taste.": [],
    "Homer, Dante and Shakespeare were the great writers of their age; in art, only Raphael and Michelangelo could compare.": [],
    "The nineteenth century's adoration of Raphael is in large part Grimm's doing.": [],
